summary: This is an FBI Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) evidence envelope form documenting the transfer of intercepted communications evidence, likely related to the Epstein investigation. The form indicates it contains original magnetic tape recordings from a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring.
keyFacts: Document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form for intercepted communications.
Evidence includes original magnetic tape recordings from a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring.
Form includes multiple custody signatures indicating chain of evidence handling.
Document references Case Agent and Supervising Agent fields, suggesting an active investigation.
Form includes fields for intercept date, place, and data transfer for permanent storage.
